# StartMission — Phase 1 of the runtime action protocol.
#
# Sent: sim_supervisor_node → mission_control_node
#
# Carries the chosen mission. mission_control_node drives mode_manager
# to bring up the right lifecycle nodes with the right strategy flag,
# emits periodic heartbeats while configure/activate is in flight, and
# reports ready/failed at the end. Cancellable — switching mission
# during this window re-enters Phase 1 for the new mission without a
# full container restart.
#
# Once `ready=true` arrives, the supervisor opens a separate
# RuntimeControl action for Phase 2.

# ---------------- Goal ----------------
# Mission identifier. Must be one of:
#   "trackdrive" | "autocross" | "accel" | "skidpad"
string mission

---
# ---------------- Result ----------------
# True if all autonomy lifecycle nodes reached `active` inside the
# startup window; false if any failed to configure/activate.
bool ready

# Human-readable diagnostic when ready=false. Empty string on success.
string message

---
# ---------------- Feedback ----------------
# Heartbeat. mission_control_node emits these as `activate_mode` makes
# progress so a crashed startup is detectable from the supervisor side
# without polling every lifecycle node directly.
#
# Stage values, in roughly the order they appear during a successful
# bring-up:
#   "configuring"                        — initial beat at goal accept
#   "configuring cone_detection_node"    — per-node, per-transition (#387);
#   "cone_detection_node configured"        derived from /mode_manager/progress
#   "activating cone_detection_node"        events in mission_control_node.
#   "cone_detection_node activated"         Verb forms: configuring /
#   "configuring slam_node"                 configured, activating /
#   "slam_node configured"                  activated, deactivating /
#   …                                       deactivated, cleaning_up /
#                                           cleaned_up.
#   "warming_up"                         — fallback beat during quiet
#                                          gaps (e.g. Numba JIT not
#                                          yielding).
#   "ready"                              — all done, result imminent
#   "failed"                             — terminal; result follows
#   "<node> <transition> failed: <msg>"  — terminal w/ diagnostic
#   "<node> <transition> timeout: <msg>" — same
#
# Consumers (sim_supervisor's relay, Mission Control web's spinner)
# should treat unknown stage strings as informational rather than
# hard-keying on the list above — the per-node variants are open-ended
# in node names and may grow as new autonomy nodes get lifecycle-managed.
string stage
builtin_interfaces/Time stamp
